The “Four Part” Test

Qualifying for R&D Tax Credits

The “Four Part” Test is derived from compliance to IRS guidelines.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: In each of the four categories there is a list of contemporaneous documentation needed to build a defensible R&D audit report.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Part 1 - Eliminate Uncertainty

The activity must be intended to discover information that would eliminate uncertainty concerning the capability or method for developing or improving a product, process, technique or formula, or the appropriateness of the product or process design.

 

Document types can include:

• Failure Reports / Test Results

• Function Specifications

• Project Descriptions or Epics (Trello, Jira, etc.) 

• Design Review Process Descriptions

• Meeting Minutes / Memos

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Part 2 - Technological in Nature

The activity performed must attempt to discover information that is technological in nature by relying on principles of:

• Physical Science

• Biological Science 

• Computer Science 

• Engineering

 

Document types can include:

• Schematics

• Architecture / Design Documents

• Technical Diagrams/Specifications 

• Patents (applications, etc.)

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Part 3 - Process of Experimentation

Experimentation activities involve:

• Evaluating alternatives

• Confirming a hypothesis through testing or modeling

• Refining or discarding a hypothesis

 

Document types can include:

• White Papers

• Project Proposals

• Experiment Results (ex. A/B test results) 

• R&D Interviews

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Part 4 - Functional Development / Permitted Purpose

The activity must relate to a new or improved:

• Function

• Performance 

• Reliability

• Quality

 

Document types can include:

• Marketing Information 

• Brochures, etc.

• Company Overview

• Pitch Decks

• Published Articles
